{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775867340616,"sessionID":"ses_2860fd53cffeIZwy9rcWI6qt9T","part":{"id":"prt_d79f12723001VjD8WG8rvJJxIw","messageID":"msg_d79f036c6001XK0ia0JAqo8vsb","sessionID":"ses_2860fd53cffeIZwy9rcWI6qt9T","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-92035b9b766444b5906eb9144d9b53df","state":{"status":"error","input":{"content":"# Proposal: CLI Publish Command Implementation\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR:** AR-022 — CLI publish command  \n**Module:** cmd/cli  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** L\n\nThis proposal outlines the implementation of the `publish` command for the AgentCube CLI tool, which enables publishing/deploying AI agents to either AgentCube (via AgentRuntime CR) or standard Kubernetes (via Deployment + NodePort Service).\n\n## Background\n\nThe AgentCube CLI (`kubectl-agentcube`) is a developer tool for managing AI agent lifecycle operations including packaging, building, publishing, invoking, and status checking. The `publish` command is a critical component that handles the deployment phase, supporting multiple deployment targets and image preparation strategies.\n\n## Requirements\n\nBased on the CLI toolkit specification, the publish command must:\n\n### Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Dual Provider Support**\n   - Support `agentcube` provider (AgentRuntime CR deployment)\n   - Support `k8s` provider (standard Deployment + Service deployment)\n\n2. **Image Preparation**\n   - Local build mode: Use Docker push to registry\n   - Cloud build mode: Use cloud-provided image URL\n   - Support registry authentication (username/password)\n\n3. **Publishing Workflow**\n   - Validate workspace and metadata\n   - Prepare container image (push or use provided URL)\n   - Deploy to Kubernetes (either AgentRuntime CR or standard K8s resources)\n   - Update metadata with deployment information\n   - Provide rich console output with progress indicators\n\n4. **Configuration Options**\n   - Version specification (semantic versioning)\n   - Image URL (for cloud mode)\n   - Registry authentication\n   - Deployment configuration (region, namespace, replicas, node_port)\n   - Cloud provider selection\n\n### Non-Functional Requirements\n\n1. **Error Handling**\n   - Comprehensive error messages with actionable guidance\n   - Verbose mode with detailed logging\n   - Graceful handling of partial failures\n\n2. **User Experience**\n   - Rich console output using Typer and Rich\n   - Progress indicators for long-running operations\n   - Clear success/failure feedback\n\n3. **Compatibility**\n   - Python 3.10+\n   - Kubernetes client integration\n   - Docker SDK for image operations\n\n## Implementation Design\n\n### Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    CLI Layer                         │\n│              (agentcube/cli/main.py)                 │\n│                 publish() command                    │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n                      ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                 PublishRuntime                       │\n│            (agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py)    │\n│                                                      │\n│  publish()                                           │\n│    ├─ _publish_cr_to_k8s() [AgentCube provider]     │\n│    └─ _publish_k8s() [K8s provider]                 │\n│                                                      │\n│  _prepare_image_for_publishing()                     │\n│    ├─ _prepare_local_image() [Docker push]          │\n│    └─ _prepare_cloud_image() [Cloud URL]            │\n└─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────┘\n                      │\n          ┌───────────┴───────────┐\n          ▼                       ▼\n┌───────────────────┐   ┌───────────────────┐\n│  AgentCubeProvider │   │ KubernetesProvider│\n│  (agentcube/      │   │  (agentcube/      │\n│   services/       │   │   services/       │\n│   agentcube_      │   │   k8s_provider.py)│\n│   provider.py)    │   │                   │\n└───────────────────┘   └───────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Key Components\n\n#### 1. CLI Command (`agentcube/cli/main.py`)\n\n```python\ndef publish(\n    workspace: str = typer.Option(\".\", \"-f\", \"--workspace\"),\n    version: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--version\"),\n    image_url: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-url\"),\n    image_username: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-username\"),\n    image_password: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--image-password\"),\n    description: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--description\"),\n    region: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--region\"),\n    cloud_provider: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--cloud-provider\"),\n    provider: str = typer.Option(\"agentcube\", \"--provider\"),\n    node_port: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--node-port\"),\n    replicas: Optional[int] = typer.Option(None, \"--replicas\"),\n    namespace: Optional[str] = typer.Option(None, \"--namespace\"),\n    verbose: bool = typer.Option(False, \"--verbose\"),\n) -> None:\n```\n\n#### 2. PublishRuntime (`agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py`)\n\n**Methods:**\n- `publish(workspace_path, **options)`: Main orchestration method\n- `_publish_cr_to_k8s()`: Deploy using AgentRuntime CR\n- `_publish_k8s()`: Deploy using standard K8s resources\n- `_prepare_image_for_publishing()`: Image preparation orchestration\n- `_prepare_local_image()`: Docker push workflow\n- `_prepare_cloud_image()`: Cloud URL validation\n- `_update_publish_metadata()`: Update metadata with deployment info\n\n#### 3. Provider Services\n\n**AgentCubeProvider:**\n- `deploy_agent_runtime()`: Create/update AgentRuntime CR\n- CR specification with readiness probes, timeouts, and session management\n- Integration with workload manager and router\n\n**KubernetesProvider:**\n- `deploy_agent()`: Create Deployment and Service\n- `wait_for_deployment_ready()`: Rollout monitoring\n- Support for node port configuration\n\n#### 4. Supporting Services\n\n**DockerService:**\n- `push_image()`: Push to registry with authentication\n- Image tagging and credential management\n\n**MetadataService:**\n- Load/save/update agent metadata\n- Validation of workspace configuration\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### Phase 1: Core Infrastructure (Week 1-2)\n\n1. **PublishRuntime Class Structure**\n   - Create class skeleton with all required methods\n   - Implement constructor with verbose and provider parameters\n   - Add logging infrastructure\n\n2. **Metadata Integration**\n   - Implement workspace metadata loading\n   - Validate required fields for publishing\n   - Add version management\n\n3. **Image Preparation Framework**\n   - Implement `_prepare_image_for_publishing()` orchestration\n   - Create stubs for local and cloud preparation methods\n\n### Phase 2: Local Build Mode (Week 3-4)\n\n1. **Docker Integration**\n   - Implement `_prepare_local_image()` method\n   - Integrate with DockerService for image operations\n   - Handle registry authentication\n\n2. **Image Tagging and Push**\n   - Implement semantic version tagging\n   - Stream push progress to console\n   - Handle push failures gracefully\n\n3. **Error Handling**\n   - Validate image availability before push\n   - Provide actionable error messages\n   - Implement rollback on failure\n\n### Phase 3: AgentCube Provider (Week 5-6)\n\n1. **AgentRuntime CR Deployment**\n   - Implement `_publish_cr_to_k8s()` method\n   - Create CR specification with all required fields\n   - Handle readiness probe configuration\n\n2. **AgentCubeProvider Integration**\n   - Implement or verify `deploy_agent_runtime()` method\n   - Set default session timeouts\n   - Configure workload manager and router URLs\n\n3. **Status Verification**\n   - Verify CR creation success\n   - Extract agent endpoint from response\n   - Update metadata with deployment info\n\n### Phase 4: K8s Provider (Week 7-8)\n\n1. **Standard K8s Deployment**\n   - Implement `_publish_k8s()` method\n   - Create Deployment and Service resources\n   - Handle node port configuration\n\n2. **Rollout Monitoring**\n   - Implement `wait_for_deployment_ready()` monitoring\n   - Support configurable timeout (default 120s)\n   - Handle rollout failures\n\n3. **Service Configuration**\n   - Create NodePort Service\n   - Validate node port range (30000-32767)\n   - Return service URL for user access\n\n### Phase 5: CLI Integration (Week 9-10)\n\n1. **Typer Command**\n   - Implement `publish()` command in main.py\n   - Add all required options with appropriate defaults\n   - Integrate with PublishRuntime\n\n2. **Rich Console Output**\n   - Add progress spinners for long operations\n   - Format success messages with key information\n   - Color-coded error messages\n\n3. **Error Handling**\n   - Implement `_handle_error()` integration\n   - Verbose mode with detailed tracebacks\n   - Exit with appropriate codes\n\n### Phase 6: Testing and Validation (Week 11-12)\n\n1. **Unit Tests**\n   - Test PublishRuntime methods\n   - Test provider integration\n   - Test error handling scenarios\n\n2. **Integration Tests**\n   - End-to-end publish workflow\n   - Test both providers\n   - Test image preparation strategies\n\n3. **User Acceptance Testing**\n   - Test with example agents\n   - Validate console output\n   - Test error scenarios\n\n## Dependencies\n\n### Required Dependencies\n\nFrom `pyproject.toml`:\n- `typer[all]>=0.9.0` - CLI framework\n- `pydantic>=2.0.0` - Data validation\n- `pyyaml>=6.0` - YAML parsing\n- `httpx>=0.24.0` - HTTP client\n- `docker>=6.0.0` - Docker SDK\n- `rich>=13.0.0` - Rich console output\n- `packaging>=23.0` - Version handling\n- `kubernetes>=28.0.0` - Kubernetes client (optional)\n\n### External Dependencies\n\n- Docker daemon (for local build mode)\n- Kubernetes cluster (for deployment)\n- Container registry (for image push)\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n### Technical Risks\n\n1. **Docker Integration Complexity**\n   - Risk: Docker SDK variations and authentication issues\n   - Mitigation: Comprehensive error handling and clear error messages\n\n2. **Kubernetes API Changes**\n   - Risk: CRD schema changes affecting AgentRuntime CR\n   - Mitigation: Version-specific client-go integration\n\n3. **Image Push Failures**\n   - Risk: Network issues, authentication failures, registry downtime\n   - Mitigation: Retry logic, progress monitoring, graceful failure handling\n\n### Operational Risks\n\n1. **Partial Deployment States**\n   - Risk: Image push succeeds but deployment fails\n   - Mitigation: Transaction-like behavior with rollback capability\n\n2. **Resource Conflicts**\n   - Risk: Existing deployments with same name\n   - Mitigation: Update vs. create logic, user warnings\n\n3. **Timeout Issues**\n   - Risk: Long-running deployments exceeding timeouts\n   - Mitigation: Configurable timeouts, progress reporting\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n### Functional Success\n\n- [ ] Publish command successfully deploys agents to both providers\n- [ ] Image preparation works for both local and cloud modes\n- [ ] Metadata is correctly updated with deployment information\n- [ ] All CLI options are properly implemented and validated\n\n### Quality Success\n\n- [ ] Code coverage > 80%\n- [ ] All linting checks pass (ruff, mypy)\n- [ ] Console output is clear and informative\n- [ ] Error messages provide actionable guidance\n\n### User Experience Success\n\n- [ ] Command completes within acceptable timeframes\n- [ ] Progress indicators are visible during long operations\n- [ ] Verbose mode provides useful debugging information\n- [ ] Help documentation is comprehensive\n\n## Timeline\n\n| Phase | Duration | Deliverables |\n|-------|----------|--------------|\n| Phase 1 | 2 weeks | Core infrastructure, metadata integration |\n| Phase 2 | 2 weeks | Local build mode with Docker integration |\n| Phase 3 | 2 weeks | AgentCube provider implementation |\n| Phase 4 | 2 weeks | K8s provider implementation |\n| Phase 5 | 2 weeks | CLI integration and Rich output |\n| Phase 6 | 2 weeks | Testing and validation |\n| **Total** | **12 weeks** | **Production-ready publish command** |\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. Review and approve this proposal\n2. Set up development environment with required dependencies\n3. Create feature branch for implementation\n4. Begin Phase 1 implementation\n5. Regular progress reviews with stakeholders\n\n## Appendix\n\n### Example Usage\n\n```bash\n# Local build with AgentCube provider\nkubectl-agentcube publish --workspace ./my-agent \\\n  --version v1.0.0 \\\n  --image-url registry.example.com/my-agent:1.0.0 \\\n  --image-username admin \\\n  --image-password secret \\\n  --provider agentcube\n\n# Cloud build with K8s provider\nkubectl-agentcube publish --workspace ./my-agent \\\n  --version v1.0.0 \\\n  --cloud-provider huawei \\\n  --provider k8s \\\n  --node-port 30080 \\\n  --replicas 3\n\n# Verbose mode for debugging\nkubectl-agentcube publish --workspace ./my-agent \\\n  --version v1.0.0 \\\n  --verbose\n```\n\n### Metadata Update Example\n\nAfter successful publish, `agent_metadata.yaml` is updated with:\n\n```yaml\nagent_name: my-agent\nversion: v1.0.0\nimage:\n  url: registry.example.com/my-agent:1.0.0\n  tag: 1.0.0\nagent_id: agent-abc123\nagent_endpoint: http://my-agent.default.svc.cluster.local:8080\nk8s_deployment:\n  type: AgentRuntime\n  namespace: default\n  name: my-agent\n  status: deployed\n```","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md"},"error":"You must read file /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/proposal.md before overwriting it. Use the Read tool first","time":{"start":1775867340607,"end":1775867340612}}}}
